text: Gorgeous place of worship. It is clean, beautifully structured and well maintained. The acoustics are also brilliant because no microphone was needed. It is elegant, tasteful and it felt safe.

I visited the Chesed-El Synagogue during the My Community Festival. It is a privilege because, if I am not wrong, it is the first time that this synagogue is opened to the public. Thank you for the hospitality. The place is really beautiful.
Beautiful quaint synagogue worth visiting to appreciate the Jewish community in Singapore.
A beautiful place, nice people. Recommended.
A beautiful synagogue with a rich history and a very friendly and knowledgeable rabbi.
